abstract: Argentine prosecutor Javier de Luca drops charges against Pres Cristina Fernandez de Kirchner, who was accused of conspiring to shield Iranians suspected of planning 1994 bombing of Jewish community center in Buenos Aires; de Luca, who took on case after original prosecutor Alberto Nisman died from gunshot wound before presenting evidence to Congress, says there is no crime on which to base investigation.
lead_paragraph: The accusation that President Cristina Fernández de Kirchner and her foreign minister had conspired to shield Iranians in a bombing appeared to dissolve.

headline.main: Federal Prosecutor Drops Kirchner Conspiracy Case
headline.print_headline: Federal Prosecutor Drops Kirchner Conspiracy Case
